Reasoning: The paper introduces a new graph invariant called shrub-depth and focuses on its logical aspects. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the relationship between shrub-depth and clique-width, which falls under the category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper deals with the characterization of the lower levels of the MSO1 transduction hierarchy of simple graphs, which is related to Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Finally, since the paper deals with graphs, it could also be classified under Computational Geometry (cs.CG).
